Masazu ISONO, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES FIDELITY & GUARANTY COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 2, 1932. Culp & Culp, of Oakland, Cal,, for appellant. Pord & Johnson and F. A. Cutler, all of San Francisco, CaL, for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon oral motion of counsel for appellant, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be dismissed fo-r failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
